Our room overlooked the street, but was quiet and very comfortable.	Our room was located in the front of the hotel, and with the windows open, the street noise was almost unbearable.	We were given a room facing the street that was hot and, once Spanish celebrations started, very noisy.	The neighbourhood is very quiet for a big city, so getting a good night's sleep was not a problem!	We had a twin room facing the street, (which was very quiet), decent sized bathroom, and spotlessly clean.	We were on the street side, so there was some street noise at night.